post1.caption:
A lovely few days spent on Bozcaada (Tenedos) Island. We stayed at @tasadabozcaada which has a perfect location just a few minutes walk from the center of town.

On one side of the town lies a clock tower, Greek taverns and white-washed houses. While on the other you’ll find a mosque and elements of Ottoman architecture. 🏖 With amazing beaches, colourful cafes, delicious food and great wine - it makes for the perfect weekend getaway.

💙 THINGS TO DO 💙

1. Enjoy a Turkish breakfast in one of the cute cafes
2. Wander around the charming town
3. Swim at one of the many empty beaches
4. Try a glass of local wine, the island is famous for its grapes
5. Shop at the local artisan’s market
6. Feast on a delicious dinner of fresh locally caught fish
7. Visit the Museum & Castle to learn more about the islands history
8. Grab some drinks and snacks and watch the sunset from Polente Lighthouse near the wind turbines

post2.caption:
Lazy mornings at @hillsidebeachclub 🌿

Relaxing on the jetty at Silent Beach where pine trees meet the sea. This beach is adults only and the perfect place to switch off and be at one with nature. Lounge on the beach with a good book, take a dip in the crystal clear water or go for a massage at Sanda Spa located right behind the sunbeds. Take time to make your soul happy 💙
